{"word":"stagnation","priority":"★★★","meanings":[{"part_of_speech":"noun","definition":"停滞、不振、沈滞","english_definition":"a state of not flowing or moving; a state of inactivity or sluggishness.","examples":[{"sentence":"The economy is suffering from stagnation.","translation":"経済は停滞に苦しんでいる。"},{"sentence":"There has been a period of stagnation in the housing market.","translation":"住宅市場は停滞期に入っている。"},{"sentence":"The stagnation of water in the pond led to algae growth.","translation":"池の水が停滞したため、藻が発生した。"}],"collocations":["economic stagnation (経済停滞)","wage stagnation (賃金停滞)","intellectual stagnation (知的停滞)","cultural stagnation (文化停滞)"],"synonyms":["inactivity","sluggishness","dullness","decline","recession","standstill","immobility"],"antonyms":["growth","progress","development","expansion","advancement","flow","movement"]},{"part_of_speech":"noun","definition":"(精神的・感情的な)行き詰まり、マンネリ","english_definition":"a lack of development, advancement, or progressive movement.","examples":[{"sentence":"He felt a sense of stagnation in his career.","translation":"彼はキャリアに行き詰まりを感じていた。"},{"sentence":"The relationship had reached a point of stagnation.","translation":"その関係は行き詰まりを迎えていた。"},{"sentence":"She feared intellectual stagnation if she stayed in the same job too long.","translation":"彼女は同じ仕事に長く留まると、知的な行き詰まりを恐れていた。"}],"collocations":["creative stagnation (創造性の停滞)","emotional stagnation (感情的な停滞)","spiritual stagnation (精神的な停滞)"],"synonyms":["rut","impasse","deadlock","plateau","lack of progress","lack of growth"],"antonyms":["renewal","invigoration","stimulation","dynamism"]}],"etymology":{"value":"由来はラテン語の「stagnare」（停滞する、水が溜まる）から来ており、さらに「stagnum」（池、沼）に遡る。英語の「stagnation」は17世紀に、文字通り水が動かない状態を表す言葉として使われ始め、その後、経済や社会、個人の成長が停滞する状態を指すようになった。","priority":"★★☆"},"pronunciation":{"ipa":"/stæɡˈneɪʃən/","syllables":"stag-na-tion"},"inflection":{"notes":"名詞であり、複数形はありません。"},"usage_notes":{"explanation":"「**stagnation**」は、主に経済、社会、個人の成長などが停滞し、進展が見られない状態を指す言葉です。経済分野では、成長率が低い状態や、景気が低迷している状態を「economic stagnation」と表現します。個人のキャリアや人間関係においては、進展や変化がなく、マンネリ化している状態を指すことがあります。文字通りに水が淀んでいる状態を表すこともあります。","priority":"★★★"},"common_mistakes":{"examples":[{"incorrect":"✗ The stagnation is very high in this country.","correct":"✓ The level of stagnation is very high in this country. / ✓ This country is experiencing a high level of stagnation.","note":"「stagnation」は状態を表す名詞なので、それ自体が「高い」という表現は不自然です。停滞の程度を表す場合は、「level of stagnation」や「high level of stagnation」のように表現します。"},{"incorrect":"✗ We need to remove the stagnate.","correct":"✓ We need to remove the stagnation.","note":"「stagnate」は動詞であり、「stagnation」は名詞です。文脈に応じて使い分けましょう。ここでは名詞の「stagnation」が適切です。"},{"incorrect":"✗ The stagnation is making me feel depress.","correct":"✓ The stagnation is making me feel depressed.","note":"「depress」は動詞ですが、ここでは「depressed」（落ち込んだ、憂鬱な）という形容詞を使うのが適切です。"}],"priority":"★★☆"},"related_words":{"derivatives":["stagnant (形容詞: 停滞した、よどんだ)","stagnate (動詞: 停滞する、よどむ)"],"idioms_phrases":["break the stagnation (停滞を打破する)","overcome stagnation (停滞を克服する)"],"priority":"★★★"},"level_frequency":{"CEFR":"C1","frequency_google_ngram":"中頻度 (Moderate frequency) - ビジネス、経済、社会科学分野でよく使われる。","priority":"★☆☆"},"readability_explanation":{"level":"C1","text":"「**stagnation**」は、経済や社会、個人の成長などが停滞し、進展が見られない状態を指す言葉です。経済用語としては、成長率が低い状態や景気低迷を意味し、個人や組織においては、進歩や変化がなく、マンネリ化している状態を表します。抽象的な概念を扱うため、理解にはある程度の語彙力と背景知識が必要です。専門的な文脈でよく使われるため、ニュース記事や経済に関するレポートなどで頻繁に目にするでしょう。"},"example_sentences":[{"sentence":"The government is trying to address the issue of economic **stagnation**.","translation":"政府は経済停滞の問題に取り組もうとしている。","type":"noun","meaning_category":"経済停滞"},{"sentence":"The company's lack of innovation led to **stagnation** in sales.","translation":"その会社の革新性の欠如が、売上の停滞につながった。","type":"noun","meaning_category":"停滞 (ビジネス)"},{"sentence":"He felt a sense of **stagnation** in his personal life.","translation":"彼は私生活に行き詰まりを感じていた。","type":"noun","meaning_category":"行き詰まり (個人的)"},{"sentence":"The **stagnation** of water in the swamp created a breeding ground for mosquitoes.","translation":"沼の水の停滞は、蚊の繁殖地を作り出した。","type":"noun","meaning_category":"停滞 (水)"}]},"related_terms": [
